    "recap_headline": "Ohio State Buckeyes | Ohio State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "COLUMBUS, Ohio\n\u2013\nAlex Bemis\nwent yard twice as the Ohio State baseball team (10-12) earned a seven-inning, 14-4 victory against Butler (5-19) on Sunday to secure to series sweep.\nGame Recap\nButler got on the board first, taking a 2-0 lead in the top of the first after a two-run home run.\nThe Bulldogs extended their lead to 3-0 in the top of the second off an RBI single to left field.\nMason Eckelman\nwalked to lead off the bottom of the second inning, followed by a single to right field from\nDane Harvey\n.\nMaddix Simpson\nwas then hit by a pitch to load the bases.\nSteven Cavaco\nthen singled to left field, scoring Eckelman to put the Buckeyes on the board. With one out,\nCJ Reid\nwalked, allowing\nDane Harvey\nto score. With a full count and loaded bases,\nAlex Bemis\nhit a grand slam to left center to give Ohio State the lead, 6-3.\nIn the top of the third, Butler added a run on a Buckeye error, but Ohio State continued to possess the lead, 6-4.\nA sacrifice fly from Harvey in the bottom of the third scored Eckelman to put the Buckeyes back ahead by three, 7-4.\nIn the bottom of the fifth,\nHenry Kaczmar\nhit a solo home run to extend the Buckeye lead, 8-4.\nIn the bottom of the sixth inning, with Reid on base after a single to left field, Bemis hit another home run to push two more runs across for the Buckeyes. With one out,\nNoah Furcht\nhit an infield single, followed by a single from Eckelman. A double from Harvey sent Furcht home and a sacrifice fly from Simpson scored Eckelman to give Ohio State a commanding eight-run lead, 12-4.\nIn the bottom of the seventh, Kaczmar walked it off for Ohio State with a two-RBI single to right field, to secure the Buckeyes the 14-4 victory and the series sweep.\nBuckeyes by the Numbers\nThis is the Buckeyes' second series sweep of the season after winning all three games in a series against Saint Louis on opening weekend. This is Ohio State's first sweep at Bill Davis Stadium since 2023, when the Buckeyes won three again rival Michigan to close out the season.\nThe Buckeyes run-ruled the Bulldogs in all three games of the series.\nBemis hit two home runs and recorded six RBIs, which are both career-highs.\nBemis, Kaczmar, Eckelman and Harvey led the team in hits with two each.\nEvery Buckeye in the lineup scored at least one run, with Eckelman and Reid leading the team with three runs scored each.\nPierce Herrenbruck\n(2-1) earned the win on the mound. He struck out four and gave up two earned runs on five hits in 5.0 innings pitched.\nUp Next\nThe Buckeyes will play at Wright State at 5 p.m. on Tuesday, March 24.\n#GoBucks",
